                            <comment id="78573" author="adilger" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2014 09:13:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think the test is correct:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;        if [ $(lustre_version_code $SINGLEMDS) -lt $(version_code 2.4.51) ]; then
                [ $I -eq $MAX ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; return 0
        else
                [ $I -gt $MAX ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; return 0
        fi
        error_exit &quot;current dir size $I, previous limit $MAX&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The check for older &amp;lt;= 2.4.51 MDSes seems OK - if the directory size is equal to the limit then the test has passed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t understand the else clause, however.  That returns success (0) if the directory grew larger than the limit, which I thought the patch was trying to fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are also a few other places in the test that could be fixed.  &quot;while [ ! $I -gt $MAX ]&quot; should instead be &quot;while [ $I -lt $MAX ]&quot;, &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="78541" author="bogl" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2014 22:32:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;another, in b2_5:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c2381ac8-a4ac-11e3-a92a-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c2381ac8-a4ac-11e3-a92a-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;frequency is getting worse.  maloo now says:&lt;br/&gt;
Failure Rate: 26.00% of last 100 executions &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;all branches&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe this needs a raise in priority.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
